# Trivy vulnerability ignore list.
# Format: one advisory ID per line. See https://trivy.dev/latest/docs/configuration/filtering/

# CVE-2023-36308 — panic (index out of range) in github.com/disintegration/imaging
# when decoding a crafted TIFF file (scanner.go, Grayscale path).
#
# Accepted, not fixed:
#   - Transitive only: threatcl/spec -> goccy/go-graphviz -> imaging. go-graphviz
#     calls imaging.Resize on images it renders itself; threatcl never decodes
#     untrusted TIFF input, so the vulnerable path is unreachable (confirmed by
#     govulncheck: 0 reachable vulnerabilities).
#   - Severity LOW; the advisory itself doubts any real security consequence.
#   - No patched imaging release exists (project abandoned since v1.6.2, 2019),
#     and go-graphviz v0.2.10 (latest) still requires it — nothing to bump to.
# Tracked/dismissed as Dependabot alert #58 and code-scanning alert #83.
CVE-2023-36308
